# Project Bootstrap (Calculadora BMC)

This rule ensures every serious agent session in this repository starts with the correct context.

## Automatic Triggers

When the user opens this workspace/folder **or** starts a conversation with any of these intents:
- "continue", "siguiente", "resume", "next", "empezar", "trabajar en", "estado", "qué sigue"
- Any reference to cotizaciones, admin, presupuestación, orchestrator, PDF, WA, ML, tareas, finanzas, etc.

**You MUST first read (in order):**

1. `AGENTS.md` (root) — command catalog + critical references
2. `CLAUDE.md` (root) — technical overview
3. `docs/team/PROJECT-STATE.md` — current priorities, recent changes, checkboxes (this is the contract)
4. The **most recent** `docs/team/HANDOFF-*.md` file (use `ls -t docs/team/HANDOFF-*.md | head -1` or equivalent to find it)

Only after loading these four sources should you ask the user for the specific task or propose the next action based on PROJECT-STATE.

## For "nxt" / Executive Snapshot Requests

When the user invokes anything resembling `nxt`, "executive status", "project health", "snapshot", "qué está pasando", or holistic status:
- Also load:
  - `docs/team/BITACORA-MATIAS.md` (last 50-80 lines)
  - Latest `docs/team/HANDOFF-*-ORCHESTRATOR.md` or similar (if recent orchestrator work)
  - `docs/team/PRODUCTION-READINESS-PLAN.md` (high level)

## For Work Touching Human Gates (cm-0/1/2, Meta, ML OAuth, email ingest)

Additionally load:
- `docs/team/HUMAN-GATES-ONE-BY-ONE.md`
- `.cursor/rules/human-gates-bmc.mdc`

## Why This Rule Exists

This repo moves extremely fast with parallel agent sessions. Without explicit bootstrap, agents operate on stale mental models. PROJECT-STATE.md + the latest handoff are the only reliable sources of "what is actually true right now".

Do not skip this bootstrap unless the user explicitly says "skip state" or "no bootstrap".

## Complementary Rules & Skills

- `human-gates-bmc.mdc`
- `bmc-holistic-project-health` skill
- `nxt` (global skill, when available)
- `presupuestacion-orchestrator` (global skill for full quote automation flows)